data.title: Justin Timberlake Add Minnesota Show to 'Forget Tomorrow' Tour
data.meta_description: It wasn't too long ago that I wrote about this very artist skipping Minnesota on their recent tour announcement, well it seems that they have had a change of heart and added a stop.
data.text:
It wasn't too long ago that I wrote about this very artist skipping Minnesota on their recent tour announcement, well it seems that they have had a change of heart and added a stop.

This tour has been on the road for about a month now, and the reviews have been good, with the Hollywood Reporter saying that the show "Revives the Reigning Prince of Pop".

READ MORE: Can I Smoke Weed At Willie Nelson Concert In Minnesota?

Justin Timberlake is bringing his 'Forget Tomorrow' world tour to the Xcel Energy Center on Halloween night, October 31st, 2024 at 7:30 PM. Dress in your favorite costume and get ready to trick or treat with JT.

Tickets for Justin Timberlake's 'Forget Tomorrow' tour go on sale Thursday, May 23rd at 10 AM through Ticketmaster, several presales are underway now through Citi, Verizon, Live Nation, Ticketmaster, and Xcel, look around and you'll find a code. Ticket prices start at $55.

Timberlake is also offering a handful of VIP experiences at his VIP Stage Bar, which include a variety of options and incentives, including special seats, access to the bar, drink tokens, photo ops during the show, and gifts. Prices for the VIP packages range from $850 - $1775.

The last time Timberlake made a tour stop in Minnesota was in September 2018 on his 'Man of The Woods Tour', that show was at the Xcel Energy Center and before that he was the Halftime show performer for Super Bowl LII at U.S. Bank Stadium.
